    {
      "id": "PopularPost181654",
      "post_content": "I think the main thought behind this card was that besides having an [Act of Treason](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Act of Treason) on your turn, you could also do use this card in an opponent's turn to grab and untap one of his attackers and use it to block another one from them to kill them each other.  \nThe power restriction just makes it a bit tricky to use.  \n  \nRegarding the use in this duel deck, i think it's pretty decent: You have various sorceries and instants, and small creatures like [Skirk Prospector](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Skirk Prospector) and [Cinder Wall](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Cinder Wall) lying in your graveyard.  \nIf there's a [Knight Exemplar](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Knight Exemplar) or [Kinsbaile Cavalier](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Kinsbaile Cavalier), you can either choose one of them or another knight from their side, either way some knights will get weaker and make it easer for you to kill at least one. [Knight of Meadowgrain](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Knight of Meadowgrain) for example nets you some life and can be used to kill it and either of them (if just one of them is on the field)  \nGrab their [Kn](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Kn)... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "Mode",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost181654\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl08_post\">I think the main thought behind this card was that besides having an <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Act of Treason\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Act of Treason\">Act of Treason</a> on your turn, you could also do use this card in an opponent's turn to grab and untap one of his attackers and use it to block another one from them to kill them each other.<br/>The power restriction just makes it a bit tricky to use.<br/><br/>Regarding the use in this duel deck, i think it's pretty decent: You have various sorceries and instants, and small creatures like <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Skirk Prospector\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Skirk Prospector\">Skirk Prospector</a> and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Cinder Wall\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Cinder Wall\">Cinder Wall</a> lying in your graveyard.<br/>If there's a <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Knight Exemplar\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Knight Exemplar\">Knight Exemplar</a> or <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Kinsbaile Cavalier\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Kinsbaile Cavalier\">Kinsbaile Cavalier</a>, you can either choose one of them or another knight from their side, either way some knights will get weaker and make it easer for you to kill at least one. <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Knight of Meadowgrain\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Knight of Meadowgrain\">Knight of Meadowgrain</a> for example nets you some life and can be used to kill it and either of them (if just one of them is on the field)<br/>Grab their <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Kn\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Kn\">Kn</a>... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 181654)\"